
lhc-regress is installable from the top-level directory.

  cabal install -f lhc-regress


To run the testsuite, simply execute 'lhc-regress'. No command line arguments are required.



A testcase consists of:
  {name}.[l]hs                                           # Program source
  {name}.expected.stdout AND/OR {name}.expected.stderr   # Expected output from stdout and stderr.
  Additional parameters can are:
    {name}.mustfail                                      # Empty file indicating the test is known to fail.
    {name}.args                                          # List of command line arguments separated by spaces.
